Key Match Events: Freddie Freeman knuckled a two-run single to center.
Teoscar Hernández blasted a two-run double over Judge’s head in the gap.
Giancarlo Stanton hit a sacrifice fly in the sixth inning.
Blake Treinen got a first-pitch fly ball from Stanton and a sweeping, swinging strikeout of Rizzo to end the eighth inning.
Walker Buehler pitched the ninth inning and got the final out.
Post-Match Reflections: Aaron Judge expressed pride in the team's resilience after the come-from-behind win.
Manager Dave Roberts emphasized the importance of the team's resilience and fight.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers fell behind by five runs in the first three innings.
The Yankees' defense capitulated in the fifth inning, allowing the Dodgers to tie the game.
The Dodgers manufactured two eighth-inning runs off of two sacrifice flies.
Walker Buehler emerged for the save in the ninth despite being an impending free agent.
